text: Mitsuka Ikeda (born 15 September 1932) is a Japanese gymnast. She competed in seven events at the 1956 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1932 births Category:Living people Category:Japanese female artistic gymnasts Category:Olympic gymnasts of Japan Category:Gymnasts at the 1956 Summer Olympics Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
